commit.message:
ALC255 layout=69 Headphones Fix (#858)

* New layout-id=69 for ALC255 / Acer Aspire 3 A315-56-327T

Microphones of the headsets do not work out of the box, their verbs need to be send manually in ALC255. Instructions are in the codec dump ALC255/69.txt

* revert back the broken verb

it introduces white noise after sleep

* layout.xml, platforms.xml and PinConfigs fixup

added verbs and adjusted layout and platforms.xml for layout=69

* ConfigData & WakeConfigData fixup

fixed static noise after power state change (AC to BAT) by setting connector types for Line In (0x19) and HP Out (0x21) to Combination, instead of 1/8" Stereo/Mono. also fixed pin sense of 0x19 (0x22)

current bug: sound disappears on headsets after some time when internal microphone is activates and enters sleep state. for now, it can be fixed by unplugging the headset & plugging it back in. this only happens when the laptop wakes up after sleep.

* removed LineIn input

on this layout, every time when power state changed from AC to BAT, headphones were producing static noise. on previous commits i tried to fix it by setting up connector types but actually the problem was the sound card itself. unlike other laptops, this laptop puts Node 0x19 to sleep when it's not in use, to be precise when there's no sound activity. i solved this problem by removing Line In input altogether. additionally, users of this laptop must use one of the headphone patches for ALC255 (such as ALCPlugFix-Swift)

release.description:
**Changes:**
ALC255 layout=69 Headphones Fix (#858)

* New layout-id=69 for ALC255 / Acer Aspire 3 A315-56-327T

Microphones of the headsets do not work out of the box, their verbs need to be send manually in ALC255. Instructions are in the codec dump ALC255/69.txt

* revert back the broken verb

it introduces white noise after sleep

* layout.xml, platforms.xml and PinConfigs fixup

added verbs and adjusted layout and platforms.xml for layout=69

* ConfigData & WakeConfigData fixup

fixed static noise after power state change (AC to BAT) by setting connector types for Line In (0x19) and HP Out (0x21) to Combination, instead of 1/8" Stereo/Mono. also fixed pin sense of 0x19 (0x22)

current bug: sound disappears on headsets after some time when internal microphone is activates and enters sleep state. for now, it can be fixed by unplugging the headset & plugging it back in. this only happens when the laptop wakes up after sleep.

* removed LineIn input

on this layout, every time when power state changed from AC to BAT, headphones were producing static noise. on previous commits i tried to fix it by setting up connector types but actually the problem was the sound card itself. unlike other laptops, this laptop puts Node 0x19 to sleep when it's not in use, to be precise when there's no sound activity. i solved this problem by removing Line In input altogether. additionally, users of this laptop must use one of the headphone patches for ALC255 (such as ALCPlugFix-Swift)

commit.message:
ALC255 layout=69 ConfigData Fix (#824)

* New layout-id=69 for ALC255 / Acer Aspire 3 A315-56-327T

Microphones of the headsets do not work out of the box, their verbs need to be send manually in ALC255. Instructions are in the codec dump ALC255/69.txt

* revert back the broken verb

it introduces white noise after sleep

* layout.xml, platforms.xml and PinConfigs fixup

added verbs and adjusted layout and platforms.xml for layout=69

* ConfigData & WakeConfigData fixup

fixed static noise after power state change (AC to BAT) by setting connector types for Line In (0x19) and HP Out (0x21) to Combination, instead of 1/8" Stereo/Mono. also fixed pin sense of 0x19 (0x22)

current bug: sound disappears on headsets after some time when internal microphone is activates and enters sleep state. for now, it can be fixed by unplugging the headset & plugging it back in. this only happens when the laptop wakes up after sleep.

Add id12 for ALC22 and id36 for ALC235 (#806)

* Add id12 for ALC222

Add id12 for ALC222. The line out Jack works well in Lenovo Tianyi 510s-07IMB.

* Add id 36 for ALC235

Add id 36 for ALC235. All three Jacks work well in Lenovo Tianyi 510pro-18ICB.

* Add id12 for ALC222 and id36 for ALC235

I found PinConfigs.kext cannot be edited by Xcode. So I edit it by Plist edit. Then debugged successfully at the end. Hope this PR useful.

Fix hdmi audio for 400 series 0x06C8 HD audio (#778)

* fix hdmi audio for 400 series 0x06C8 HD audio

The "old" patch sets the device id to 0x9D70 which doesn't work with hdmi audio.

This commit sets the device id to 0xA170 which also works with HDMI audio.

* Sync changelog

commit.message:
Added ALC1220A Layout 13 for Asus ProArt Z690-Creator WiFi (#760)

* Added ALC1220A Layout 13 for Asus ProArt Z690-Creator WiFi

Added Layout 13 for the ALCS1220A codec on Asus ProArt Z690-Creator WiFi. This layout supports:

Input:
(1) Mic (rear and front)
(2) Line In

Output:
Line Out (green, rear)
Rear (black, rear)
C/Sub (orange, rear)
Headphone (front)

There is no Optical Digital Output on this motherboard, hence this layout ID does not include this.

* Update Platforms13.xml

Combined rear Line Out and Headphone Out into same <array> group to enable auto-switching.

commit.message:
Improvement Realtek ALC289 layout-id 87 for Alienware m15 (#671)

in general, a few updates to fix the microphone.

Good:
- Switch mode audio output (e.g. between int & jack audio)
- Balance sound output L/R
- Mute control
- Internal speaker
- Internal mic

Still need to fix:
- Ext mic A.K.A Headset mic (3.5mm combojack audio)
- A littlebit crackling (almost unhearable/unnoticeable, only IEM on my test. acceptable in my ears opinion:) )

release.description:
**Changes:**
Improvement Realtek ALC289 layout-id 87 for Alienware m15 (#671)

in general, a few updates to fix the microphone.

Good:
- Switch mode audio output (e.g. between int & jack audio)
- Balance sound output L/R
- Mute control
- Internal speaker
- Internal mic

Still need to fix:
- Ext mic A.K.A Headset mic (3.5mm combojack audio)
- A littlebit crackling (almost unhearable/unnoticeable, only IEM on my test. acceptable in my ears opinion:) )

commit.message:
Add new layout 17 for ALC280 (#591)

This layout is a mix of 13, 15 & 16 such that there will be 2 devices listed in the preferences `Internal Speaker/Line Out` depending on if theres something plugged in the rear green plug, and `Headphones`. You can manually select between these two devices in the preferences or on the sound icon on the top bar.

The main limitations lie with the hardware and with apples decision to have line-out override the headphones. The hardware limitation is that the internal speaker cannot not function if there is something in the line-out plug because they share the same AMP etc. So it only makes sense to have this part auto-switch. And because of the apple decision we really need to manually select that part.

release.description:
**Changes:**
Add new layout 17 for ALC280 (#591)

This layout is a mix of 13, 15 & 16 such that there will be 2 devices listed in the preferences `Internal Speaker/Line Out` depending on if theres something plugged in the rear green plug, and `Headphones`. You can manually select between these two devices in the preferences or on the sound icon on the top bar.

The main limitations lie with the hardware and with apples decision to have line-out override the headphones. The hardware limitation is that the internal speaker cannot not function if there is something in the line-out plug because they share the same AMP etc. So it only makes sense to have this part auto-switch. And because of the apple decision we really need to manually select that part.

commit.message:
Add ALC235 layout-id 17 for Lenovo ThinkCentre Tiny M720q (#513)

Inputs:
25 - Internal Mic (Combo with HP Out Front Jack when headset with integrated mic is inserted)
26 - External Mic (Dedicated Front Jack setup as Audio Line-In port)

Outputs:
20 - Internal Speaker Out
33 - Headphones Out (Dedicated Front Jack)

Based on ALC235 layout-id 21 for Lenovo C530 Desktop PC by Andres ZeroCross with some small changes to Pin Configuration and added M720q ConfigData.
